HEADWORD: Hairsplitting
<hw>Hair"split`ting</hw> <pr>(-t⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Making
excessively fine or trivial distinctions in reasoning; overly
subtle.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or practice of making
trivial distinctions.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ancient <qex>hairsplitting</qex> technicalities of special
pleading.</q> <rj><qau>Charles Sumner.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

